101
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:34,800
his perspective not only on life,

102
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:37,240
but his perspective on ministry.

103
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:40,080
And he does not take the approach,

104
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:42,320
as we'll look through the text of scripture,

105
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:45,399
of doing the same thing that the Judaizers are doing.

106
00:03:45,399 --> 00:03:48,279
He's not gonna just get into a mud fighting contest

107
00:03:48,279 --> 00:03:50,279
and throw in mud at these guys.

108
00:03:50,279 --> 00:03:52,080
He's going to share with them

109
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:54,160
the call that God's placed upon his life

110
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:56,240
and his perspective on ministry

111
00:03:56,240 --> 00:04:00,039
and what he endeavors to accomplish with his life.

112
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:01,880
You know, in verse number 18,

113
00:04:01,880 --> 00:04:04,119
and we'll get through the whole text this morning,

114
00:04:04,119 --> 00:04:06,100
but I wanna draw your attention to verse 18

115
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:10,759
as we look here this morning at this text of scripture,

116
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:11,600
the Bible says,

117
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:16,600
for not he that commendeth himself is approved.

118
00:04:18,119 --> 00:04:20,519
And we know some people that commend themselves.

119
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,920
You get into a conversation with them

120
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,239
and they just want you to know how good they are

121
00:04:25,239 --> 00:04:26,820
and how wonderful they are.

122
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:30,320
And they are the gift in your life.

123
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:33,200
And I mean, they are just all about themselves.

124
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:34,320
And here it says,

125
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:38,239
for not he that commendeth himself is approved,

126
00:04:38,239 --> 00:04:42,519
but whom the Lord commendeth.

127
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:45,239
And what a great verse of scripture

128
00:04:45,239 --> 00:04:49,839
for us to understand the mindset of the apostle Paul.

129
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:52,920
It reminds us really of what Paul had said earlier

130
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:53,799
in this book.

131
00:04:53,799 --> 00:04:57,100
Maybe you wanna turn back a few pages in chapter number five

132
00:04:57,100 --> 00:04:59,040
of second Corinthians chapter five.

133
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:02,799
And remember Paul said this in verse number nine,

134
00:05:02,799 --> 00:05:03,640
he says,

135
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:07,359
wherefore we labor that whether present or absent,

136
00:05:07,359 --> 00:05:10,200
we may be accepted of him.

137
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,200
He then says this in verse number 15 of the same chapter

138
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:15,359
