this is not the apostle Paul talking about salvation.

163
00:06:15,660 --> 00:06:18,299
He was saved and he was secure

164
00:06:18,299 --> 00:06:21,579
because of what Christ did on the cross of Calvary.

165
00:06:21,579 --> 00:06:26,299
This morning, your salvation is based upon your acceptance

166
00:06:26,299 --> 00:06:28,820
of the free gift of eternal life

167
00:06:28,820 --> 00:06:32,440
that was paid for with the precious blood of Christ.

168
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,739
There's no other name under heaven given among men

169
00:06:34,739 --> 00:06:38,059
whereby we must be saved.

170
00:06:38,059 --> 00:06:41,179
As an appointed unto man wants to die,

171
00:06:41,179 --> 00:06:43,380
but after this, the judgment

172
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:46,820
and every one of us have a sin issue.

173
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:51,820
We are born sinners and sin must be paid for.

174
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:56,559
And sin can only be paid for and has been paid for

175
00:06:56,559 --> 00:07:00,820
with the blood of Jesus Christ over 2000 years ago,

176
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:04,940
when he hung upon that cruel cross and he bled and died

177
00:07:04,940 --> 00:07:07,179
and he was buried and he rose,

178
00:07:07,179 --> 00:07:09,440
conquering sin, death and the grave.

179
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:14,399
He is alive forevermore and he is the savior,

180
00:07:14,399 --> 00:07:15,700
the only savior.

181
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:19,399
And the question this morning is, is he your savior?

182
00:07:19,399 --> 00:07:22,720
And if you say, yes, he is my savior,

183
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:25,720
the people that Paul is writing to, Paul was saved.

184
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:29,179
He's writing to the church in Corinth of saved people.

185
00:07:29,179 --> 00:07:32,040
And he's saying to them, when we live life,

186
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:36,679
we live desiring God's approval.

187
00:07:36,679 --> 00:07:39,480
We don't misunderstand this morning,

188
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:41,339
Paul's not saying we're gonna live this way

189
00:07:41,339 --> 00:07:43,359
so that we can earn salvation,

190
00:07:43,359 --> 00:07:45,119
so that we can get to heaven.

191
00:07:45,119 --> 00:07:47,859
No, you can't get to heaven by your good works.

192
00:07:47,859 --> 00:07:49,760
For by grace are you saved through faith

193
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,299
and that not of yourselves, the gift of God,

194
00:07:52,299 --> 00:07:55,640
not of works, lest any man should boast.

195
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:59,600
The redemption of your soul and of the souls of mankind

196
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,880
is precious and it was paid for

197
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,880
with the precious blood of Christ.

198
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:06,640
And he offers the gift of eternal life.

199
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:08,519
Brother Deal and I and Joseph and Holly,

200
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:10,000
we're sitting around the table last night,

201
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:12,519
talking over dinner, and we're talking about

202
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:14,839
some of the visitation opportunities that we had

203
00:08:14,839 --> 00:08:17,760
and different things that he's been able to experience

204
00:08:17,760 --> 00:08:20,000
and just recently opportunities.

205
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,880
And one of the things that I mentioned

206
00:08:21,880 --> 00:08:24,440
is that you try to get people to understand

207
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:27,399
that a gift by definition is something

208
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:29,040
that someone has paid for.

209
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:32,440
You can't earn a gift.

210
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:34,280
You can't buy a gift.

211
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:38,440
A gift is paid for by someone else.

212
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:40,960
And the gift of God, which is eternal life,

213
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:44,280
has been paid for by God, the Lord Jesus Christ,

214
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,559
with his precious blood.

215
00:08:46,559 --> 00:08:49,880
And so you can't earn it, you can't go forth

216
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,599
and try to buy it, no.

217
00:08:51,599 --> 00:08:53,080
It's already been paid for,

218
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:56,000
you must simply accept or receive it.

219
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,320
The Bible says that he came to his own,

220
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,640
his own received him not, but as many as received him,

221
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,400
to them gave he power to become the sons of God,

222
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:04,599
even to them that believe on his name.

223
00:09:04,599 --> 00:09:07,599
And so this morning, my salvation,

224
00:09:07,599 --> 00:09:12,559
my certainty of going to heaven was settled 28 years ago

225
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:14,840
when I trust that Christ is my personal savior

226
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:17,719
and I am secure in the hand of God.

227
00:09:17,719 --> 00:09:22,719
The Bible tells us, if you look in John 10 and 1 Peter,

228
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:27,880
that we know his voice and we have eternal life

229
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:28,799
and we shall never perish.

230
00:09:28,799 --> 00:09:29,640
Who is that?

231
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:30,679
Those that have been saved.

232
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:35,799
So when Paul talks about desiring God's approval,

233
00:09:35,799 --> 00:09:40,239
really I believe what he's talking about is living a life

234
00:09:40,239 --> 00:09:45,159
in such a way that we're seeking God's smile.

235
00:09:45,159 --> 00:09:47,039
If I could use that terminology this morning,

236
00:09:47,039 --> 00:09:50,000
and it reminds me of what Fannie Crosby said,

237
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,520
having that desire as revealed to us in that song,

238
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:55,880
my savior, first of all,

239
00:09:55,880 --> 00:09:58,559
and his smile shall be the first to welcome me.

240
00:09:58,559 --> 00:09:59,840
You think about that.

241
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:04,520
and the desire of living our lives for God's approval.

242
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:06,400
So as we look through 2 Corinthians chapter number 10,

243
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,020
if you're taking notes, notice with me,

244
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:10,240
first of all, Paul's approach.

245
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,540
In verses one through six, the apostle Paul,

246
00:10:12,540 --> 00:10:15,440
as he begins to answer and to instruct the people

247
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:18,980
in Corinth, he's going to reveal to them his approach,

248
00:10:18,980 --> 00:10:22,000
his approach to life, his approach to ministry,

249
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,800
very particularly, and we find that if we could

250
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:27,160
summarize his approach in one statement,

251
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,740
it would be this, to be like Jesus.

252
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:33,400
To be like Jesus, and can I tell you this morning,

253
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:36,640
as believers, as disciples, followers of the Lord

254
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:40,280
Jesus Christ, your approach to life and my desire

255
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:43,640
for life should be to be like Jesus.

256
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,720
They were called Christians first in Antioch, why?

257
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:49,080
Because those in Antioch observed their behavior

258
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,320
and they said they're like Christ,

259
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,440
and they're called Christians, and they were first

260
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:57,020
called disciples, remember Jesus, he calls them

261
00:10:57,880 --> 00:11:01,180
disciples, and now the word Christian,

262
00:11:01,180 --> 00:11:03,740
and we carry that term and we use it,

263
00:11:03,740 --> 00:11:07,020
